==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Counterlath
<hw>Coun"ter*lath`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Building)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A batten laid lengthwise between
two rafters to afford a bearing for laths laid crosswise.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any lath laid without actual measurement between two
gauged laths.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>Any of a series of laths nailed to
the timbers to raise the sheet lathing above their surface to afford a
key for plastering.</def> <sd>(d)</sd> <def>One of many laths used in
preparing one side of a partition or framed wall, when the other side
has been covered in and finished.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Counterman</ent>⟦br⟧
